      </section>

      <!-- ===== §6 GATEWAY ===== -->
      <section id="s6" class="in-mod">
        <header class="in-mod-h">
          <span class="in-mod-n">06</span>
          <h2>Gateway message pipeline</h2>
          <span class="in-mod-tag">messaging</span>
        </header>

        <p class="in-tldr"><b>TL;DR.</b> A Slack / Telegram / Teams / WhatsApp message arrives, gets normalized to a <code>MessageEvent</code> dataclass, runs through a <code>SessionStore</code>, fires through <code>HookRegistry</code> (the gateway's own bus, distinct from <code>PluginManager._hooks</code>), reaches an LRU-cached <code>AIAgent</code> instance, streams back via <code>GatewayStreamConsumer</code>, and ends in <code>DeliveryRouter</code>.</p>

        <p>The <code>merge_pending_message_event()</code> step coalesces rapid-fire messages (photo bursts, multi-line splits) into a single agent turn — keeps the LLM call count down on chatty users. The <code>register_post_delivery_callback()</code> mechanism lets background work (review, bubble cleanup) defer until after the user has seen the response, masking latency.</p>

        <!-- INFOGRAPHIC F — gateway pipeline -->
        <figure class="in-fig">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 720 560" role="img" aria-labelledby="figF-title" class="in-svg">
            <title id="figF-title">Gateway message pipeline — 10 steps</title>

